<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2017/09/15/spring-session-mongodb-2-0-0-m3-released">Spring Session MongoDB 2.0.0.M3 released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/43e9a9d63f7f4f9891c9fcd592b89cfa?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/gturnquist">Greg Turnquist</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2017-09-15 18:10:37.67">September 15, 2017</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3026" href="/blog/2017/09/15/spring-session-mongodb-2-0-0-m3-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Dear Spring Community,</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Spring Session MongoDB 2.0.0.M3 is released. It is based on:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li> <p><a href="https://spring.io/blog/2017/09/15/spring-session-2-0-0-m4">Spring Session 2.0.0.M4</a></p> </li>
<li> <p><a href="https://spring.io/blog/2017/09/11/spring-data-ingalls-sr7-and-kay-rc3-released">Spring Data Kay-RC3</a></p> </li>
<li> <p>Reactor Bismuth-M4</p> </li>
<li> <p><a href="https://spring.io/blog/2017/09/11/spring-framework-5-0-rc4-available-now">Spring Framework 5.0.0.RC4</a></p> </li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In this release, several new features have been added to simplify using it with your Spring WebFlux application.</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="prettyprint highlight"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java">@EnableMongoWebSession
public class SpringWebFluxConfig {

}</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>All you must do is apply the <code>@EnableMongoWebSession</code> to any of your Spring configuration classes to activate session support with MongoDB. Additionally, you must provide a <code>ReactorMongoOperations</code> Spring bean, but if you’re using Spring Boot’s <code>spring-boot-starter-data-mongodb-reactive</code> starter, this is already provided.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2017/09/15/spring-session-mongodb-2-0-0-m3-released">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
